        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/y/e19b73/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-08-27T12:27:20.097Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hello everyone,</p>\n<p>I have the following request:</p>\n<p>My girlfriend’s iPhone is broken and always switches off after three minutes. She now has a new iPhone.<br>\nShe urgently needs the Signal chats on her new iPhone.</p>\n<p>Unfortunately, a ‘traditional’ transfer is not possible because the old phone switches off after three minutes and the connection is lost before then.</p>\n<p>It’s very strange, but Signal doesn’t seem to offer any backup functions if the device is broken? I can’t imagine that such a large company would allow such a big gap in its service offering. I can’t possibly be the only person who wants to back up their data/chats. Not to mention that EU law could also see consumer rights at risk if no backup is possible, if interpreted strictly.</p>\n<p>So my question to you all is: what can I do to get the Signal chats from the old iPhone to the new iPhone if the classic data transfer doesn’t work?</p>\n<p>Is Signal planning to introduce a backup system?</p>\n<p>Thank you very much for your support and the time you are investing in me.<br>\nYouCouldBeMine</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 3,
        "updated_at": "2025-08-27T12:27:20.097Z",
