        "id": 274137,
        "name": null,
        "username": "Stephan",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/8baadc/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-08-27T20:14:45.268Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Yes, Signal on iPhone does not yet support backup at all. But it is currently be worked on and it is in closed beta testing:</p>\n<aside class=\"quote quote-modified\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"69984\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/greyson-signal/48/2005_2.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <div class=\"quote-title__text-content\">\n      <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/public-signal-backups-testing/69984\">Public Signal Backups Testing</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/announcements/call-for-testing/96\"><span data-category-id=\"96\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #0088CC; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF; --parent-category-badge-color: #ED207B;\" data-parent-category-id=\"5\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category --style-square --has-parent\" title=\"Calls for testing by the Signal team (outside of regular Beta Feedback).\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Call for Testing</span></span></a>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    TL;DR You can test the new Signal Backups feature on Android on our staging servers. Grab the self-updating apk <a href=\"https://updates.signal.org/static/android/nightlies/backup/Signal-Android-nightly-backup-universal-release-7.47.0-nightlyBackup-2025-06-25-18-07-32.apk\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">here</a>! \n\nHello, everyone! \nMany of you are aware that we’ve been working on a new end-to-end encrypted backup system for quite a while. Well, today, we’re finally ready to start testing it with external users <img width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/images/emoji/apple/slightly_smiling_face.png?v=14\" title=\"slightly_smiling_face\" alt=\"slightly_smiling_face\" class=\"emoji\"> \nThe new backup system fulfills so many of the things people have wanted for so long: \n\nHosted by Signal, so your data is safe even if you made a local back…\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n\n<p>But I doubt that it would help even if backup feature would be already available as the broken phone shuts down after 3 minutes and it might not be enough time to perform a full backup.</p>\n<p>Not sure if another approach might help you: as far as I know if you link another device to your main device then all messages + images from last 45 days can be synched to new linked device.</p>\n<p>If that works (but even here I think 3 minutes might be too less to fully synch) then you could keep for now your old device as main device and link the new device.</p>",
